    definition: 'Cohort analysis is a behavioral analytics technique that groups users by a shared characteristic or experience within a defined time span and tracks their behavior over time. Instead of looking at aggregate metrics like total Monthly Active Users which can be misleading, cohort analysis reveals how different groups of users behave over their lifecycle. Common cohort types include acquisition cohorts grouped by when users signed up, behavioral cohorts grouped by specific actions taken, and size-based cohorts grouped by purchasing power. The analysis typically examines retention rates, revenue per user, or engagement metrics for each cohort over successive time periods.',
