    whyItMatters: 'Cohort analysis separates genuine growth from temporary spikes. It reveals user retention patterns, identifies when users drop off, and measures whether product improvements actually change user behavior. It is essential for understanding product-market fit, calculating Customer Lifetime Value, and making data-driven product decisions.',
